            "@type": "Dataset",
            "identifier": "369-Moriyama-deuterateRaman",
            "name": "Multiple deuteration of triphenylphosphine and live-cell Raman imaging\nof deuterium-incorporated Mito-Q",
            "description": "All aromatic C–H bonds of triphenylphosphine (PPh3) were efficiently replaced by C–D bonds using Ru/C and Ir/C co-catalysts in 2-PrOH and D2O, an inexpensive deuterium source. Furthermore, non-radioactive and safe deuterium-incorporated Mito-Q (drug candidate) was prepared from deuterated PPh3 and used for the live-cell Raman imaging to evaluate the mitochondrial uptake.",
